eviously reported for NiV-M. The results of this study suggest that the M proteins of henipaviruses may utilize a similar nucleocytoplasmic trafficking pathway as an essential step during viral replication in both humans and bats.,", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "McLinton, Elisabeth C", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wagstaff, Kylie M", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lee, Alexander", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Moseley, Gregory W", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Marsh, Glenn A", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Wang, Lin-Fa", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Jans, David A", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lieu, Kim G", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Netter, Hans J", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/a0d7eda365d7d525bedf2b61d114407d", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/400fdb8f212b465a94cebc9beae218afb6fefb67e8fd00f928172b541b19a63c", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/XXL3BLQI", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/XXL3BLQI", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/45d37bbd1757e45c878df6ea8d25dbc9!/b43981-46547", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "4", "pages": "563-576", "title": "Journal of General Virology,", "volume": "